title: DiResta [Pt. 2] Camper Trailer Interior
description:
In this project I execute and fabricate the interior of the camper trailer built in part one. The interior for this camper trailer was designed on paper by the client and given to us to interpret. Taylor Forrest worked hand-in-hand with the client choosing materials the best represented what was shown in the drawing. And I also made some changes along the way as far as colors and textures. The walls of this camper trailer are covered with a Formica  type laminate. The countertops are Corian. And the under cabinets are  plywood in MDF in conservation of excessive weight. Patrick Renolds did all the electrical system based on the conversations with the client and what their needs would be, and the plumbing system is designed by Taylor Forrest, a simple gray water system. Much of the research for this camper trailer project build was found on YouTube so thanks for that!!  and thank you for watching!

follow Patrick for daily electric tips

title: DiResta Make 48 & Operation Breakthrough
description:
My DiResta GIANT Razors… Now LIVE HERE: 
 https://imakeny.com/products/diresta-...
 In this video, I joined the team @gomake48 and @workbenchcon to create the ultimate fan experience for a very deserving group in Kansas City in 48 hours.  If you haven’t seen their competitions, you should check them out at www.make48.com

www.operationbreakthrough.org has created an “Ignition Lab”, a new makerspace, with the help of @killatrav foundation @87running, for teens to come and explore making and other STEM programs after school.

The fan experience will have a home in the new Ignition Lab and will serve as a place for teens to watch the games and hang out with friends.

This special build was made possible by an amazing group of sponsors who care about the mission.  I’d like to thank:

title: DiResta Basement Door Rebuild: 200+ Year Old Farmhouse
description:
My DiResta GIANT Razors… Now LIVE HERE: 
 https://imakeny.com/products/diresta-...
 Get the DiResta RAZOR Box Here: 
 https://jimmydiresta.com/the-diresta-...
 Enter My Giveaway Here: 
 https://vy.lc/423449tqwrh
  

For this woodworking and metalworking project, for the past 16 years I have intended to rebuild the basement door of my 200+ year old farm house… and finally I am doing just that! The wood for this door build is maple from the saw mill, which has been dried for over a year…. and I did leave room in the door frame for expansion. The gaps on the doorframe a will be filled in with mortar when the weather warms up.  I hope that you enjoy this project!

Than you

title: DiResta Fancy Leather Wallet
description:
Get it all here 
 https://www.weaverleathersupply.com
 My DiResta GIANT Razors… Now LIVE HERE: 
 https://imakeny.com/products/diresta-...
 In this project video I made a fancy leather wallet at the suggestion of a friend.  To be honest, I was intimidated by the design and the wallet’s construction, but did it anyway for the lessons I learned, which hopefully you will as well.  For this wallet making project I used the Weaver 303 walking foot sewing machine.  Of course, I need to make it a few more times to get the confidence in the skills necessary, but I learned a lot. A big thank you to Weaver – Enjoy!
